Four people were killed and several others sustained injuries after a truck and two mini-bus taxis were involved in a collision on the Queen Nandi Drive and Quarry Park Close intersection in KwaZulu-Natal. Netcare 911 KZN spokesperson Shawn Herbst said at approximately 6:20am on Monday morning, paramedics responded to reports of a serious collision. “On arrival to the scene, Netcare911 paramedics found that two bodies had to be removed from the wreckage by Ethekwini Fire and Rescue using the Jaws of Life,” Herbst said. Herbst said two other bodies were found at the scene of the accident. All injured patients were treated on the scene and transported to hospital by several ambulances. This cause of the accident is still unknown and will form part of a SAPS investigation. -TNA Reporter